\def\@LN@column{1}
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{2}{7}{AMLOps-AIOps platform architecture. AML domain services (blue) publish compliance events to Kafka via the outbox pattern and push telemetry to the observability stack (green). The AIOps pipeline (orange) processes signals through: Telemetry Collector $\to $ Stream Processor $\to $ ML Engine $\to $ LLM Engine $\to $ Decision Engine $\to $ Remediation Engine. Dashed arrows denote asynchronous Kafka flows and OTLP pushes; the Feedback Service closes the loop by uploading LoRA adapter weights trained on resolved incident outcomes back to the LLM Engine}{figure.caption.2}{}}
